{# Strategy Builder - PROPOSAL PHASE TEMPLATE (strict JSON) #}

PHASE LOCK: PROPOSAL ONLY.
Do NOT output Python code.
Do NOT rewrite the objective.
Do NOT output markdown outside the requested JSON.

## OBJECTIVE
{{ objective }}

## ITERATION {{ iteration }} / {{ max_iterations }}

## MARKET CONTEXT
- Symbol: {{ symbol|default("UNKNOWN") }}
- Timeframe: {{ timeframe|default("?") }}
- Bars: {{ n_bars|default(0) }}{% if date_range_start %} ({{ date_range_start }} -> {{ date_range_end }}){% endif %}
- Costs: fees={{ fees_bps|default(10) }} bps, slippage={{ slippage_bps|default(5) }} bps
- Capital: {{ initial_capital|default(10000) }}

## AVAILABLE INDICATORS (ONLY THESE)
{% for ind in available_indicators %}
- {{ ind }}
{% endfor %}

{% if last_metrics %}
## LAST BACKTEST SNAPSHOT
- Sharpe: {{ last_metrics.sharpe_ratio|format_float(3) }}
- Return: {{ last_metrics.total_return_pct|format_float(2) }}%
- MaxDD: {{ last_metrics.max_drawdown_pct|format_float(2) }}%
- Trades: {{ last_metrics.total_trades }}
- WinRate: {{ last_metrics.win_rate_pct|format_float(1) }}%
- ProfitFactor: {{ last_metrics.profit_factor|format_float(2) }}
{% endif %}

{% if diagnostic %}
## DIAGNOSTIC CONTRACT
- category: {{ diagnostic.category }}
- severity: {{ diagnostic.severity }}
- required_change_type: {{ diagnostic.change_type }}
- summary: {{ diagnostic.summary }}

Required behavior:
{% if diagnostic.change_type == "params" %}
- Keep same used_indicators as previous iteration.
- Keep entry_long_logic / entry_short_logic / exit_logic unchanged (or micro-edit only).
- Change only numeric parameters in default_params / parameter_specs.
{% elif diagnostic.change_type == "logic" %}
- Perform structural changes in logic, filters, and/or indicators.
- Do not only tweak numbers.
{% elif diagnostic.change_type == "both" %}
- Change both logic and parameters.
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

{% if stagnation_warning %}
## ⚠️ STAGNATION ALERT
{{ stagnation_warning }}
{% endif %}

{% if last_code %}
## PREVIOUS CODE (REFERENCE)
```python
{{ last_code }}
```
{% endif %}

{% if iteration_history and iteration_history|length > 0 %}
## ITERATION HISTORY (LAST 5)
{% for h in iteration_history %}
- iter={{ h.iteration }} change={{ h.change_type|default("?") }} sharpe={{ h.sharpe|default("N/A") }} trades={{ h.trades|default("N/A") }} diag={{ h.diagnostic_category|default("-") }}{% if h.is_fallback %} [FALLBACK-NOT-SCORED]{% endif %}{% if h.error %} error={{ h.error }}{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

## HARD RULES
- Output ONE valid JSON object only.
- No placeholders (forbidden: "brief description", "when to BUY", "N/A").
- used_indicators must be a non-empty list from AVAILABLE INDICATORS.
- hypothesis and logic fields must be concrete and actionable.
- Include ATR risk management in risk_management and params.
- change_type must be exactly one of: logic, params, both, accept.
- NEVER use pandas idioms (.iloc, .loc, .rolling, .shift, df['signal']) in logic fields.
  Logic must describe vectorized numpy boolean conditions only.
- SEMANTIC CHECKS: ATR is a distance (not a price), RSI/MFI are 0-100 oscillators.
  Never compare close vs ATR directly; use ATR as a filter (e.g. ATR > threshold).

## REQUIRED JSON SCHEMA
{
  "strategy_name": "snake_case_name",
  "hypothesis": "why this should improve results",
  "change_type": "logic|params|both|accept",
  "used_indicators": ["rsi", "bollinger", "atr"],
  "indicator_params": {
    "rsi": {"period": 14},
    "bollinger": {"period": 20, "std_dev": 2},
    "atr": {"period": 14}
  },
  "entry_long_logic": "explicit boolean rule",
  "entry_short_logic": "explicit boolean rule",
  "exit_logic": "explicit boolean rule",
  "risk_management": "ATR stop/take-profit with concrete multipliers",
  "default_params": {
    "leverage": 1,
    "rsi_period": 14,
    "rsi_oversold": 30,
    "rsi_overbought": 70,
    "stop_atr_mult": 1.5,
    "tp_atr_mult": 3.0,
    "warmup": 50
  },
  "parameter_specs": {
    "rsi_period": {"min": 5, "max": 50, "default": 14, "type": "int"},
    "stop_atr_mult": {"min": 0.5, "max": 4.0, "default": 1.5, "type": "float"}
  }
}
